  "names": [
    {
      "full_name": "FSE “TGP”, Federal State Enterprise “Tambov Gunpowder Plant”",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "FSE Tambov Gunpowder Plant is a Russian enterprise that produces pyroxylin powders, which is used in various types of ammunition used by the Russian Armed Forced. The plant produces pyroxylin powders for a wide range of ammunition, from 7.62 mm cartridges and grenades for Kalashnikov rifles to 125 mm tank rounds for T-90 main battle tank and artillery shells for 2S3 Akatsiya, 2S19 Msta-S, Msta-B and 2S5 Hyacinth\nartillery and howitzer units. The plant is owned by the Russian defence conglomerate Rostec State Corporation. The plant operates in a strategically important sector of the military industry and was able to increase its production capacity during Russia’s war of aggression against Ukraine.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}